The paper focuses on the impact of interdisciplinary research in the social sciences, which involves collaboration between different fields such as computer science, information retrieval, human-computer interaction, and computational engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering).
